	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> " She was a wife of  \n                  \n                     ʾaṣe Zarʾa Yāʿqob. \n                  She revolted against the emperor in 1460. As a consequence, she was beaten with rods and died shortly thereafter. \n                  Following her death the emperor took ʾƎleni.\n                  Ṣǝyon Mogasā was buried secretly by her children at a church \n                  near Dabra Bǝrhān. " .
